<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>Antoine Griezmann has expressed his desire for Lionel Messi to stay at Barcelona.</p>

<p>Messi's future at Barcelona remains unresolved after he submitted a transfer request, and Griezmann admitted that he doesn't have any inside information about whether his exalted team-mate will stay.  </p>

<p>As reported by Mundo Deportivo, Griezmann said: 'We try to have news, but what happens is between the club and him. We just hope he stays. We listen to a bit of everything but we don't know more on our part'.</p>

<p>Antoine Griezmann has expressed his desire for team-mate Lionel Messi to stay at Barcelona</p>

<p>Messi and his father Jorge have been in discussions with Barcelona but it remains to be seen whether the 33-year-old will stay at the club. </p>

<p>There is a possibility that he could see out the final year of his contract at the Nou Camp before leaving on a free transfer in 2021. </p>

<p>Messi's future at the Nou Camp remains unresolved after he submitted a transfer request</p>

<p>New Barcelona manager Ronald Koeman is tasked with overhauling the club's squad</p>

<p>The future of the Argentina superstar is just one issue that Barcelona have to address ahead of the new campaign, with new manager Ronald Koeman tasked with overhauling the squad.</p>

<p>Ivan Rakitic has already left for Sevilla, while Messi's close friend Luis Suarez is another player who could depart.</p>

<p>Barcelona are eager to respond following a hugely disappointing 2020-21 campaign which ended without them winning a trophy and included a harrowing 8-2 defeat to Bayern Munich in the Champions League.</p>
